Strict-Transport-Security (HSTS) is used to:

🛡️ 1. Force HTTPS always
Prevents browser from using HTTP
Protects sensitive data (login, cookies)

🧨 2. Stop SSL Stripping attacks
Attackers try to downgrade HTTPS → HTTP
HSTS blocks this after first visit

🔒 3. Protect session cookies

Prevents cookies from being sent over HTTP
Reduces session hijacking risk

🌐 4. Enforce secure communication across site
Ensures all future requests use HTTPS only


✅ Safe / Recommended HSTS Rule
Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
🧠 Explanation of each part
⏳ max-age=31536000

Time in seconds (1 year)

👉 Meaning:
Browser remembers rule for 1 year
Will never use HTTP during this period
